From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: ci <ci@local>
Date: 2026-05-22T05:35:00Z
Subject: [PATCH] patches/0043-fman-pcd-kg-graft-mode-nia.patch

PR14z15 (2026-05-22): silicon-truth fix for the M2 acceptance gate
CPU regression.  PR14z13 (patch 0042) grafts an ASK CC tree onto an
existing kernel-owned KG scheme by writing KGSE_CCBS via the AR-
mediated RMW primitive keygen_scheme_set_ccbs().  Live silicon
regdump on 2026-05-22 (bin/ask-pcd-regdump.py against DUT
192.168.1.190) confirmed KGSE_CCBS is correctly programmed on the
grafted schemes -- but the M2 metric did not move (6.901 Gbps PASS /
27.26%% kernel-net CPU FAIL vs. <=5%% threshold).  Every kernel-owned
scheme on every active port was carrying:

    kgse_mode      = 0x80500002    (EN | NIA_ENG_BMI | NIA_BMI_AC_ENQ_FRAME)
    kgse_ekfc      = 0x00180206    (IPSRC1|IPDST1|IPSEC_SPI|L4PSRC|L4PDST)
    kgse_spc       = 4050 / 3128 / 3118 ...   (scheme actively dispatching)
    kgse_ccbs      != 0 on slots 3 & 4         (PR14z13 graft worked)

KGSE_MODE NIA encoding (RM 8.7.4, confirmed against SDK
fsl_fman_kg.h in archived mihakralj/kernel-ls1046a-build at SHA
464df181, fm_kg_build_nia() in fman_kg.c lines 528-538):

    bits[31]        EN
    bits[30:24]     CCOBASE        (CC group base offset, 8 bits)
    bits[22:18]     NIA engine     (mask 0x007C0000)
                    FM_CTL = 0x00000000   <- route KG -> CC engine
                    PRS    = 0x00440000
                    KG     = 0x00480000
                    PLCR   = 0x004C0000
                    BMI    = 0x00500000   <- route KG -> BMI direct
    bits[17:0]      NIA action     (mask 0x0003FFFF)

The silicon dispatcher consults KGSE_CCBS ONLY when the NIA engine
field equals FM_CTL.  With NIA = BMI the scheme enqueues directly to
the kernel's per-CPU RX FQ and the CC engine is never invoked --
which is precisely the failure mode the live regdump confirms.
keygen_scheme_setup() always sets kgse_mode = (KG_SCH_MODE_EN |
ENQUEUE_KG_DFLT_NIA) at scheme-create time (fman_keygen.c line 506),
and PR14z13's keygen_scheme_set_ccbs() RMW touches ONLY kgse_ccbs --
so a freshly-grafted scheme has the CCBS pointer set but the NIA
engine still routing past the CC engine.

PR14z14 in ask_hw.c (silicon-truth 16-byte CC key layout, SIP|DIP|
SPI=0|SPORT|DPORT) is correct per kgse_ekfc but unreachable because
the CC engine never runs.

Fix
---
Extend keygen_scheme_set_ccbs() to RMW kgse_mode in the SAME AR-
mediated transaction as kgse_ccbs.  The READ AR pulls the full
scheme image into regs->fmkg_sch; we modify kgse_mode AND kgse_ccbs
in the indirect window; the WRITE AR flushes both back atomically.
Every other KGSE_* field (kgse_ekfc, kgse_mv, kgse_fqb, kgse_hc,
kgse_dv0/1, kgse_om, kgse_vsp, generic extracts) is preserved by
virtue of being re-emitted from the same indirect window the READ
just populated.

Two cases:

  ccbs != 0  (graft):
      mode = (mode & ~(KG_NIA_ENG_MASK | KG_NIA_AC_MASK))
              | KG_NIA_ENG_FM_CTL    (= 0x00000000 -- explicit for clarity)
      // CCOBASE bits[30:24] stay at whatever they were (0 for the
      // single-group cc_trees ASK uses today).

  ccbs == 0  (ungraft):
      mode = (mode & ~(KG_NIA_ENG_MASK | KG_NIA_AC_MASK))
              | ENQUEUE_KG_DFLT_NIA  (= 0x00500002 -- restore default
                                       BMI direct-enqueue NIA used at
                                       keygen_scheme_setup() time)

The masks KG_NIA_ENG_MASK (0x007C0000) and KG_NIA_AC_MASK
(0x0003FFFF) are added to fman_keygen.c next to the existing
NIA_ENG_BMI / NIA_BMI_AC_ENQ_FRAME / ENQUEUE_KG_DFLT_NIA constants.
Naming follows the SDK header (KG_NIA_*) to keep cross-reference
trivial.

Locking / atomicity
-------------------
Unchanged.  The AR READ/WRITE pair runs under fman_pcd's pcd->lock
(taken by fman_pcd_kg_graft_cc / fman_pcd_kg_ungraft_cc in patch
0042 before invoking keygen_scheme_set_ccbs).  Two fields written
inside the same indirect window flush as one atomic WRITE AR.

Compatibility
-------------
keygen_scheme_setup() and keygen_port_hashing_init() are unchanged:
they still initialise kgse_mode to ENQUEUE_KG_DFLT_NIA, which is
the correct default for an un-grafted hash-only scheme.  The NIA
rewrite happens exclusively inside keygen_scheme_set_ccbs() so non-
graft callers see no behavioural change.

Verification
------------
1. patch-health.sh --flavor ask --source release: must apply clean.
2. After CI build + ISO install on Mono DUT:
   - bin/ask-pcd-regdump.py shows kgse_mode of grafted schemes
     (slots 3 and 4 on hwports 0x10/0x11) with NIA engine bits
     cleared (mode & 0x007C0000 == 0), kgse_ccbs unchanged from
     pre-patch graft value.  Un-grafted schemes (slots 0/1/2)
     still show kgse_mode = 0x80500002.
   - kgse_spc on grafted schemes keeps incrementing.
   - bin/verify-ask-flow-offload.sh: kernel-net CPU drops to
     <=5%% while throughput stays >=2 Gbps -> M2 gate PASS.
3. On module unload (rmmod ask), regdump shows the slots that
   were grafted now have kgse_mode restored to 0x80500002 and
   kgse_ccbs back to 0 -- proves ungraft path symmetry.
---
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_keygen.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_keygen.c
@@ -94,6 +94,16 @@
 #define NIA_BMI_AC_ENQ_FRAME		0x00000002
 #define ENQUEUE_KG_DFLT_NIA		(NIA_ENG_BMI | NIA_BMI_AC_ENQ_FRAME)
 
+/* PR14z15: KGSE_MODE NIA-engine / NIA-action field masks used by
+ * keygen_scheme_set_ccbs() to flip the NIA engine between BMI
+ * (default, no CC) and FM_CTL (graft active, CC engine invoked).
+ * Silicon ignores KGSE_CCBS unless NIA engine == FM_CTL.  See RM
+ * 8.7.4 and SDK fsl_fman_kg.h fm_kg_build_nia().
+ */
+#define KG_NIA_ENG_MASK			0x007C0000
+#define KG_NIA_AC_MASK			0x0003FFFF
+#define KG_NIA_ENG_FM_CTL		0x00000000
+
 /* Hard-coded configuration:
  * These values are used as hard-coded values for KeyGen configuration
  * and they replace user selections for this hard-coded version
@@ -609,6 +619,7 @@
 	struct fman_kg_regs __iomem *regs;
 	struct keygen_scheme *scheme;
 	u32 ar_reg;
+	u32 mode;
 	int err;
 
 	if (!keygen)
@@ -631,7 +642,22 @@
 		return err;
 	}
 
-	/* Modify only kgse_ccbs in the indirect window. */
+	/* PR14z15: rewrite KGSE_MODE NIA engine + action fields in the
+	 * indirect window before flushing.  Without this, a non-zero
+	 * KGSE_CCBS is silently ignored because the silicon dispatcher
+	 * still routes KG -> BMI (the default NIA programmed at
+	 * keygen_scheme_setup() time).  CCOBASE bits[30:24] and the EN
+	 * bit are preserved -- only the NIA engine field flips.
+	 */
+	mode = ioread32be(&regs->fmkg_sch.kgse_mode);
+	mode &= ~(KG_NIA_ENG_MASK | KG_NIA_AC_MASK);
+	if (ccbs != 0)
+		mode |= KG_NIA_ENG_FM_CTL;	/* graft: KG -> CC engine */
+	else
+		mode |= ENQUEUE_KG_DFLT_NIA;	/* ungraft: KG -> BMI default */
+	iowrite32be(mode, &regs->fmkg_sch.kgse_mode);
+
+	/* PR14z13: update KGSE_CCBS (CC tree MURAM offset / 0 to clear). */
 	iowrite32be(ccbs, &regs->fmkg_sch.kgse_ccbs);
 
 	/* WRITE phase: flush the modified image back. */
